West Nile virus in the United States - WHO Update 4
-------------------------------------------------
As of Mon 23 Sep 2002, the WHO Collaborating Centre for Arthropod Borne
Viruses -- Western Hemisphere, at the Centers for Disease Control and
Prevention (CDC) has reported 1963 human cases of West Nile virus
infection, with 94 deaths occurring in 32 states and the District of Columbia.

During 2002, West Nile virus activity evidence of infections in birds,
humans, mosquitoes, and other animals (primarily horses) has been
documented in 42 states and the District of Columbia. For more information
about this outbreak see the CDC web site:

- States reporting confirmed West Nile virus infection in birds,
mosquitoes, animals, or humans between 1 Jan - 16 Sep 2002.
<http://www.cdc.gov/ncidod/dvbid/westnile/surv&control.htm>

- About the Virus, the Disease, and Its Spread
<http://www.cdc.gov/ncidod/dvbid/westnile/index.htm>

- *Prevention: Avoid Mosquito Bites to Avoid Infection
<http://www.cdc.gov/ncidod/dvbid/westnile/index.htm>

