Equine Cases of West Nile Virus Infection: 1 Jan Through 22 Sep 2002
------------------------------------------------
The total number of equine cases of illness caused by West Nile virus (WNV)
confirmed at the USDA's National Veterinary Services Laboratories (NVSL) or
reported by state officials so far this year is 6223. That is an increase
of 843 cases from 5 days ago.

The cases are from 34 states: Alabama (39), Arkansas (56), Colorado (242),
Florida (130), Georgia (25), Illinois (249), Indiana (256), Iowa (403),
Kansas (221), Kentucky (248), Louisiana (306), Maryland (2), Massachusetts
(1), Michigan (123), Minnesota (537), Mississippi (180), Missouri (174),
Montana (83), Nebraska (914), New Jersey (13), New Mexico (19), New York
(7), North Dakota (530), Ohio (203), Oklahoma (47), Pennsylvania (14),
South Carolina (2), South Dakota (573), Tennessee (79), Texas (425),
Vermont (3), Virginia (17), Wisconsin (45), and Wyoming (57).

